        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Key details\n\n- This is the **standard reduction potential** measured against the **Standard Hydrogen Electrode (SHE)**.\n- Under non-standard conditions, the potential shifts according to the **Nernst equation**: E = E° − (RT/2F) ln(1/[Cu²⁺]).\n- **Do not confuse** with the related copper couples:\n\n| Couple | E° (V vs. SHE) |\n|---|---|\n| Cu²⁺/Cu⁰ | +0.340 |\n| Cu²⁺/Cu⁺ | +0.153 |\n| Cu⁺/Cu⁰ | +0.521 |",
